# Prerequisites :: The default Anchor project test file (TypeScript) created with the anchor init command requires Node.js and Yarn. (The Rust test template is available using anchor init --test-template rust)&

#Install Node using Node Version Manager (nvm) by running the following command:&

$ curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/master/install.sh | bash

#Restart your terminal and confirm that the nvm command runs successfully:&
$ command -v nvm

#Use nvm to install Node:&
$ nvm install node

#Verify that the installation succeeded, by checking the Node version:&

$ node --version

#You will see output like the following:&

$ v23.7.0

$ cargo install --git https://github.com/solana-foundation/anchor --tag v0.30.1 anchor-cli

$ anchor --version

#anchor-cli 0.31.1
